Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Nathan Robert Bailey in court with attorney Jessica L Schuster.  Defendant Nathan Robert Bailey in custody.  Ralph M Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 13CM141, 13CM142, 13CM153, 13CM174, 13CM195, 13CM224 and 14CF105 @ 3:00 p.m. Statement of negotiated plea filed. Court has reviewed revocation summaries. State agrees with written plea agreement. State has complied with victim notification requirements, asks all court obligations be converted to civil judgment in revocation cases. Statement by Atty Schuster. Def agrees with written plea agreement. Def has nothing to say regarding revocation cases. Remarks by the Court. Will accept agreement. 13CM141 ct 1 - 30 days jail with 51 days credit. 13CM142 ct 1  - 9 months jail, concurrent to 13CM141, credit for 51 days. 13CM153 ct 3 - 9 months jail, concurrent, 51 days credit. 13CM174 ct 2 - 9 months jail, concurrent, 81 days sentence credit. 13CM195 ct 1 - 30 days jail, concurrent, ct 2 - 9 months jail, concurrent, ct 3 - 9 months jail, concurrent, 128 days credit. 13CM224 ct 2 - 9 months jail, consecutive to previously cited cases. ct 3 - 9 months jail, concurrent to ct 2 but consecutive to other cases. ct 5 - 30 days jail, concurrent to other cts, consecutive to other cases. No sentence credit. Civil judgments for court obligations. State advises balance inquiries in revocation packet. Huber for employment, medical, school and AODA requested. Court grants as allowed by jail. Postconviction rights. Court calls 14CF105 - Def waives preliminary hrg. Court reviews prelim rights, finds Def understands and waiver freely made. Probable cause. Information filed. Plea to ct 1 - no contest. Court reviews plea quest. and constitutional rights. Atty Schuster satisfied/factual basis. Court finds Def understands, accepts plea and finds guilty of ct 1. Def hs nothing to say. Court accepts agreement. Ct 1 - 6 yrs prison, 3 yrs initial confinement, 3 yrs ext. supervision, imposed and stayed, consecutive to 13CM141, 13CM142, 13CM153, 13CM174, 13CM195 and 13CM224. 3 yrs probation, AODA, counseling, costs including DNA surcharge. No sentence credit. Def advised of firearms and voting rights. Def eligible for challenge inc. and substance abuse programs.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Postconviction rights.
